# Template-override floor (TPL).
#
# This dir is the resolution root for per-artifact output-format overrides
# (vision §10): a team drops `<artifact>.md` here (e.g. requirements.md) with the
# H2 shape they want, and BOTH readers use it — the stage agent fills the
# skeleton, and the required-sections sensor verifies against the same file
# (override-before-default, keyed by the output filename stem; see
# core/tools/aidlc-sensor.ts where the default templates dir is
# `<projectDir>/aidlc/spaces/<space>/memory/templates`, via memoryTemplatesDir()).
#
# The framework ships NO default templates — resolution falls through gracefully
# to the sensor's ≥2-H2 floor when a template is absent. This `.gitkeep` only
# guarantees the dir exists in a fresh shell so the resolver's lookup is a clean
# miss rather than a missing-dir edge. Drop real `<artifact>.md` overrides here.
